div.p:
He saith, the first Adam sinned by a Tree;
whereby we were lost: and our second Adam to
redeeme us, dyed on a Tree.

Knowledge and a good life are both profitable;
but if both cannot be obtained, a good
life is to bee sought rather than much knowledge.

A soule patient for wrongs offered, is like a man
with a sword in one hand, and salve in another;
could wound, but will heale. Part. 6. cap. 26.
